WEBVTT

01:32.971 --> 01:35.721
<b>Genki Trading</b>

01:36.051 --> 01:39.141
<b>I bet we're having another 
meeting until midnight.</b>

01:39.141 --> 01:43.351
<b>Wish someone would lose their shit 
and ruin the meeting.</b>

01:44.271 --> 01:46.481
<b>What <i>is</i> a meeting? 
I don't even know anymore.</b>

01:48.271 --> 01:51.491
<b><i>This endless run of meetings 
is starting to fray everyone's nerves.</i></b>

01:53.611 --> 01:55.951
<b><i>Including mine, to be honest.</i></b>

01:56.571 --> 01:59.951
<b><i>Thankfully for me, 
I have the ultimate pick-me-up:</i></b>

01:59.951 --> 02:03.211
<b><i>if I line up at Super S's register two, 
I get to see Yamada-san's smile!</i></b>

02:03.211 --> 02:05.501
<b><i>Welcome! Thank you!</i></b>

02:05.501 --> 02:09.341
<b><i>You're the guy who always lines up 
at register two, aren't you?</i></b>

02:45.581 --> 02:47.541
<b><i>Not here tonight, huh?</i></b>

02:53.051 --> 02:54.721
<b>Thank you! Come again!</b>

02:54.721 --> 02:57.301
<b><i>Wow, perfect timing!</i></b>

02:58.261 --> 03:02.261
<b><i>...you're a fan of mine!</i></b>

03:04.351 --> 03:05.731
<b>Let me ring you up.</b>

03:08.401 --> 03:10.061
<b>Welcome.</b>

03:10.061 --> 03:12.401
<b>I-If you would, please.</b>

03:12.401 --> 03:15.361
<b>Sure thing. Do you have your point card?</b>

03:16.611 --> 03:17.361
<b>Here.</b>

03:17.661 --> 03:19.371
<b>Thank you.</b>

03:20.571 --> 03:22.331
<b>Here's your card back.</b>

03:24.451 --> 03:26.461
<b><i>I heard from Tayama-chan...</i></b>

03:26.461 --> 03:28.371
<b><i>...you're a fan of mine!</i></b>

03:31.631 --> 03:32.591
<b>Sir?</b>

03:32.591 --> 03:33.501
<b>Sir?</b>

03:33.501 --> 03:34.171
<b>Yes?</b>

03:34.671 --> 03:36.971
<b>That'll be 883 yen.</b>

03:36.971 --> 03:39.131
<b>Oh, right.</b>

03:43.061 --> 03:49.441
<b><i>I'm so grateful she still serves me, even 
after I embarrassed myself like that.</i></b>

03:50.351 --> 03:53.771
<b><i>I was the only one who took it too 
seriously! I'm such a fool! A moron!</i></b>

03:54.901 --> 03:58.611
<b><i>Please allow me to keep shopping with you!</i></b>

03:59.111 --> 04:01.531
<b><i>Spend all your money here!</i></b>

04:11.791 --> 04:15.591
<b>The client's not responding 
to the apology email I sent them.</b>

04:15.591 --> 04:18.801
<b>I'll never see my family again. 
I'm going to die...</b>

04:19.261 --> 04:21.141
<b>sitting next to this old dude.</b>

04:21.141 --> 04:22.971
<b>Oh, shush, you.</b>

04:22.971 --> 04:25.601
<b>Wait, why are you even doing overtime?</b>

04:26.221 --> 04:29.061
<b>Fixing up the newbie's spreadsheet.</b>

04:29.061 --> 04:31.311
<b>Is she taking advantage of you?</b>

04:31.311 --> 04:34.821
<b>A rookie shouldn't be handling 
this work to begin with.</b>

04:34.821 --> 04:36.531
<b>It was the chief, wasn't it?</b>

04:36.531 --> 04:40.151
<b>He's the one who believes in 
throwing them in at the deep end.</b>

04:40.151 --> 04:43.451
<b>I say he can believe in that 
<i>after</i> he cleans up their messes!</b>

04:45.411 --> 04:49.001
<b>Well, we can't complain. 
The rookie's the one who has it hardest.</b>

04:49.001 --> 04:50.211
<b>Just look at this spreadsheet.</b>

04:50.461 --> 04:53.421
<b>There's no doubt she made it 
to the best of her ability.</b>

04:54.001 --> 04:56.961
<b><i>Besides, I have my pick-me-up!</i></b>

04:56.961 --> 04:58.761
<b><i>Welcome!</i></b>

04:58.761 --> 05:00.921
<b><i>This isn't enough to get me down.</i></b>

05:00.921 --> 05:04.431
<b><i>Hey, it's Mister Big Fan over here.</i></b>

05:07.311 --> 05:08.391
<b>Ack!</b>

05:08.971 --> 05:12.981
<b>Gah! I undid all the fixes I made!</b>

05:14.151 --> 05:16.731
<b>We're partying all night!</b>

05:18.731 --> 05:20.991
<b>Thank you very much.</b>

05:20.991 --> 05:22.281
<b>Thank you.</b>

05:22.991 --> 05:24.911
<b><i>And she wasn't here.</i></b>

05:24.911 --> 05:29.661
<b><i>The universe is telling me off for looking 
to another person for a pick-me-up.</i></b>

05:30.751 --> 05:33.671
<b><i>Maybe I should pick up some kind of hobby.</i></b>

05:33.671 --> 05:35.211
<b>Sasaki-san.</b>

05:36.381 --> 05:38.251
<b>'Sup?</b>

05:40.011 --> 05:44.341
<b>I'm the only one in the smoking 
area now. Wanna join me?</b>

05:49.181 --> 05:53.521
<b>Tayama-san! 
I've been wanting to talk to you!</b>

05:54.141 --> 05:58.401
<b>How could you tell Yamada-san 
to her face that I'm a fan of hers?</b>

05:58.401 --> 06:01.531
<b>I've been dying of embarrassment 
every time I've lined up for her since.</b>

06:01.531 --> 06:03.781
<b>Yeah, and you still do it.</b>

06:05.241 --> 06:06.661
<b><i>Where is she even watching from?</i></b>

06:12.871 --> 06:15.671
<b>Sorry I did you like that, Sasaki-san.</b>

06:18.291 --> 06:21.211
<b>But it made Yamada-san really happy.</b>

06:21.211 --> 06:23.671
<b>She said as much, remember?</b>

06:23.671 --> 06:28.181
<b>I've lived too long 
to take that at face value, okay?</b>

06:28.181 --> 06:31.681
<b>Yeah? So, is that all you wanted 
to talk to me about?</b>

06:32.181 --> 06:33.681
<b>Oh, and also...</b>

06:34.231 --> 06:36.441
<b>For you, if you'd like.</b>

06:36.441 --> 06:40.941
<b>Yummy Mochi Chips</b>

06:36.691 --> 06:40.941
<b>As thanks for letting me 
smoke here the other night.</b>

06:40.941 --> 06:42.321
<b>Hey, I know these.</b>

06:42.321 --> 06:46.951
<b>You recognize Yummy 
Mochi Chips? I love them.</b>

06:46.951 --> 06:50.951
<b>They're really popular 
with the senior citizens.</b>

06:51.451 --> 06:53.621
<b><i>So now I'm entering gramps territory.</i></b>

06:54.331 --> 06:58.751
<b>I've been wanting to try them, 
so thanks, Sasaki-san.</b>

06:58.751 --> 07:01.461
<b>Well, don't just stand around. 
Have a seat and smoke one.</b>

07:01.751 --> 07:05.721
<b><i>Oh? My elderly taste actually worked out?</i></b>

07:05.721 --> 07:08.721
<b><i>Tayama-san's always 
subverting expectations!</i></b>

07:09.181 --> 07:12.601
<b>I just finished my shift, 
and I'm feeling peckish.</b>

07:12.601 --> 07:14.771
<b>Don't eat more than half.</b>

07:14.771 --> 07:17.391
<b>You don't want to go 
to bed feeling all stuffed.</b>

07:21.191 --> 07:26.321
<b>I left my smokes at work. 
I don't have any on me.</b>

07:27.451 --> 07:29.361
<b>You can have mine, then.</b>

07:29.781 --> 07:31.871
<b>I can't just bum off you.</b>

07:32.991 --> 07:34.041
<b>Here, smoke this one.</b>

07:36.711 --> 07:38.121
<b>Tayama-san...</b>

07:39.961 --> 07:43.091
<b>If you'd rather eat 
the chips instead, just say so.</b>

07:43.091 --> 07:46.471
<b>Hey, you're really perceptive.</b>

07:47.801 --> 07:51.221
<b>Do you enjoy messing 
with this old guy or something?</b>

07:51.221 --> 07:52.641
<b>Very much so.</b>

07:52.641 --> 07:54.261
<b>Yeah, I figured!</b>

07:54.601 --> 07:59.061
<b>I can't help it. You're my pick-me-up.</b>

07:59.061 --> 08:01.361
<b>Wh-What's that supposed to mean?</b>

08:01.361 --> 08:04.691
<b>It's the same deal as why you line up 
at Yamada-san's register.</b>

08:05.611 --> 08:08.071
<b>You're poking fun at me again.</b>

08:08.071 --> 08:12.451
<b>I swear I've never messed with 
Yamada-san like you're doing to me.</b>

08:12.741 --> 08:15.121
<b>Do you not get it?</b>

08:15.121 --> 08:17.961
<b>We all get our little pick-me-ups 
in different ways.</b>

08:17.961 --> 08:19.831
<b>So quit sulking,</b>

08:20.291 --> 08:22.581
<b>and come again, Sasaki-san.</b>

08:25.841 --> 08:28.471
<b>I'll have you know I am <i>not</i> sulking!</b>

08:29.011 --> 08:31.511
<b>Genki Trading</b>

08:33.301 --> 08:35.261
<b>Morning.</b>

08:35.261 --> 08:37.021
<b>Souvenirs</b>

08:35.261 --> 08:37.021
<b>go here</b>

08:37.021 --> 08:41.271
<b>Yummy Mochi Chips</b>

08:41.561 --> 08:44.021
<b>Did you hash it out with the client?</b>

08:44.021 --> 08:49.441
<b>You betcha. My highly honed 
apology skills came in handy.</b>

08:52.071 --> 08:54.161
<b>Were you the one who brought 
these mochi chips?</b>

08:54.161 --> 08:55.911
<b>How'd you know?</b>

08:55.911 --> 08:59.541
<b>Don't be silly. Do you have any idea 
how many times you've fed me these?</b>

08:59.541 --> 09:00.661
<b>Oh...</b>

09:00.661 --> 09:03.921
<b>Once you start, you can't stop.</b>

09:03.921 --> 09:06.841
<b>They go well with booze, too. 
Go ahead and take the bag home.</b>

09:06.841 --> 09:09.421
<b>Yeah, you bet I will!</b>

09:10.221 --> 09:12.931
<b>But how do you have so many?</b>

09:13.681 --> 09:16.431
<b>Did you actually buy them 
in bulk or something?</b>

09:16.431 --> 09:18.771
<b>I keep buying them 
when I go to the supermarket.</b>

09:19.181 --> 09:22.061
<b>I forgot I had some at home, 
so I ended up with extras.</b>

09:22.441 --> 09:25.231
<b>Wha? Just quit buying them, then.</b>

09:25.231 --> 09:28.531
<b>But then I wouldn't have anything 
to buy at the supermarket.</b>

09:28.531 --> 09:31.321
<b>Then just don't go 
to the damn supermarket!</b>

09:31.321 --> 09:33.821
<b>24-Hour</b>

09:31.321 --> 09:33.821
<b>Supermarket S</b>

09:39.201 --> 09:40.451
<b>Yummy Mochi Chips</b>

09:41.201 --> 09:43.581
<b><i>Just quit buying them, then.</i></b>

09:50.171 --> 09:51.471
<b>Welcome.</b>

09:55.011 --> 09:58.181
<b>These chips you always buy 
sure are good, aren't they?</b>

09:58.181 --> 10:01.851
<b>Huh? Do you like them too, Yamada-san?</b>

10:01.851 --> 10:05.731
<b>I do. I only found out recently, though.</b>

10:05.731 --> 10:09.111
<b>I got given some, and I really liked them.</b>

10:09.111 --> 10:10.981
<b>Now I keep snacking on them.</b>

10:10.981 --> 10:13.451
<b><i>Someone gave her some... recently?</i></b>

10:13.451 --> 10:15.491
<b><i>Mochi chips yummy.</i></b>

10:15.951 --> 10:19.031
<b><i>Wait, could it be?</i></b>

10:19.491 --> 10:22.001
<b><i>Are Yamada-san and Tayama-san...</i></b>

10:24.371 --> 10:27.211
<b><i>really good friends?</i></b>

10:27.291 --> 10:32.131
<b>Yummy Mochi Chips</b>

10:28.041 --> 10:29.171
<b><i>Let's have these.</i></b>

10:29.171 --> 10:31.171
<b><i>Wow, thanks!</i></b>

10:32.631 --> 10:35.011
<b>Hay fever, Yamada-chan?</b>

10:35.511 --> 10:41.351
<b>Nah. I just get the feeling some dense 
geezer out there's daydreaming about me.</b>

10:44.761 --> 10:48.391
<b>Translation: Sriram Gurunathan</b>

10:48.891 --> 10:52.521
<b>Editing & Typesetting: Geoff Mazzolini
Subtitle Timing: Krzysztof Kunc</b>

10:53.231 --> 10:56.481
<b>Quality Check: Zachary Carlysle
Translation Check: Sho Stifler</b>
